summary:
The Security Council,

Welcoming the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations operation in Cyprus, 
Noting the agreement of the Government of Cyprus to keep the UN Peacekeeping Force in Cyprus (UNFICYP) beyond 15 December 2002,

1. Reaffirms its relevant resolutions on Cyprus, particularly resolution 1251 (1999) and subsequent resolutions;
2. Extends the mandate of UNFICYP until 15 June 2003;
3. Requests a report from the Secretary-General by 1 June 2003 on the implementation of this resolution;
4. Urges the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces to rescind restrictions imposed on 30 June 2000 on UNFICYP operations and restore the military status quo ante at Strovilia;
5. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
